<br>{{Borderimage|id=1|image=162 - 1.png|caption=An image of Level 162.|width=450px|align=center}}<br>
<center><span style="text-shadow: 1px 1px 10px #4c6fd9;font-family:Rubik Puddles;font-size: 45px;background:linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(62, 113, 189, 1), rgba(115, 161, 230, 1), rgba(62, 113, 189, 1)); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;"> ◆ Description. </span></center>

<div class="fade-in" style="animation-duration:5s"><span style="color: white; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #789fde, 0em 0em 1.0em #789fde;font-family:Bubbler One">
Level 162 is an expansive complex of waterways that resembles an indoor waterpark, whose appearance changes wherever someone goes within the structure; these changes often affect the time of day and lighting, along with environmental features such as fog or rain.

The general appearance of Level 162 consists of beige concrete walls contrasted with marble-tiled flooring, with air vents and drowning alarms embedded into the walls. These items serve no purpose, as they are indefinitely inactive with no electrical components linked to them. Pool noodles and rubber floaties may also be found scattered across the poolside; these objects may also be accompanied by wet swimming attire. Any attempt to place these objects into the pools causes them to teleport back to their original position; in rare cases, the object entirely vanishes, and any attempt to remember it becomes futile.

The layout of Level 162 appears littered with pools of warm water that vary in shape and size; some may be small streams, while others may be lake-sized. However, all pools within the level are shallow and cannot be swam in whatsoever. The confines of these pools may contain spray fountains that constantly eject water at a low rate; most appear as mushrooms with primary-colored caps and white stems. Secondary colored fountains have been reported to exist within Level 162; however, they are rare. 


<br>{{Borderimage|id=1|image=162-3.webp|caption=Photograph of a Sticky Centipiede nest located in Level 162.|width=350px|align=center}}<br>
The pools in Level 162 may also contain fish and other aquatic life, including goldfish and koi carp. These fish cannot be harmed in any way, with most attacks phasing through their forms, suggesting that the fish may not be physical life forms but an illusion created by the level. 

On occasion, these fish have also been found suspended in the air, moving but remaining stationary for a set amount of time before returning to the water. Interacting with the fish during this phenomenon will cause them to dissipate similarly to the poolside objects, most likely due to the destabilization of their form; however, unlike the poolside objects, the fish materialize only a few seconds after vanishing.

Aquatic plantlife may also be found growing in the more damaged areas of Level 162, with forms resembling seaweed and lemongrass found within the frontrooms. Lilypads and Lotus Flowers may also be seen floating in the lazy rivers on occasion. Any contact with these plants may induce lethargy until the wanderer leaves the pool, though the wanderer affected will not fall asleep during this state.

The plants within Level 162's pools release massive amounts of oxygen into the water, often creating a mist at the top that emits a scent similar to mint; this mist is known to lower the wanderer's cortisol levels, moisturize the skin, and increase the regeneration of cell tissue. The regenerative properties cannot retattach limbs however; with the regeneration only able to heal large gashes and trauma to the body. Along with the fact that applying the mist to a wound for too long will cause hallucinations and spontanteous thrombosis.

<br>{{Borderimage|id=1|image=162-4.jpg|caption=An image of the center of current Rivertown.|width=350px|align=center}}<br>

Multiple instances of play structures can be found within Level 162's confines. These play structures are constructed of painted metal; the paint is usually a similar beige to the level's walls, but other colors have been documented. These structures never go beyond the level's ceiling, although these areas can scale quite high; with the largest within Level 162 being Rivertown, which is around the size of a small village. The stability of these structures may change over time due to water erosion; sometimes, they may collapse in on themselves due to the instability of the framing. It is often advised to avoid these broken-down structures for this reason.

The slides that accompany the structures are usually chutes or simple flat slides, painted blue or red with patterns. The same water that fills the pools flows through the slides at high speeds. Sliding down these streams isn't advised due to the risk of injury and potential disruption to the level's water system. Most slides serve to transport water through the level, ensuring all pools are maintained with water and never empty. This allows the level's power to function and keeps the water fresh, preventing it from remaining still for too long.

<center><span style="text-shadow: 1px 1px 10px #4c6fd9;font-family:Rubik Puddles;font-size: 45px;background:linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(62, 113, 189, 1), rgba(115, 161, 230, 1), rgba(62, 113, 189, 1)); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;"> ◆ Entities. </span></center>
The only recorded instances of entities within Level 162 consist of [[Entity 17|Kats]] and [[Entity 60|Sticky Centipedes]], which can be found resting by the pools and swimming through the more river-esque areas of the level, respectively.

