===<center><span style="text-shadow: 1px 1px 10px #4c6fd9;font-family:Rubik Puddles;font-size: 45px;background:linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(62, 113, 189, 1), rgba(115, 161, 230, 1), rgba(62, 113, 189, 1)); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;"> ◆ Tezo's Art Supplies - Chlorinestream Studio. </span></center>===

Status: Active

Population: 20

A well-known branch of Tezo's, found within the west sector of Level 162. The members of the group usually create cosmetic accessories as souvenirs, which are often obtainable by buying them with cascadan zhou. All funds from the purchases go towards the Rivertown Survivor Association and other charities within the backrooms, usually the [[Backrooms Red Cross]]. This branch of Tezo's is also quite popular due to their high stock of materials and gemstone trading, with multiple very positive reviews under their name.

===<center><span style="text-shadow: 1px 1px 10px #4c6fd9;font-family:Rubik Puddles;font-size: 45px;background:linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(62, 113, 189, 1), rgba(115, 161, 230, 1), rgba(62, 113, 189, 1)); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;"> ◆ Republic of Aurielle - Rivertown. </span></center>===

Status: Exterminated/Restoration In Progress

Once a prosperous settlement of the [[Republic of Aurielle]], Rivertown is currently a ruin of play structures and residences. Now predominantly inhabiting temporary camps and Sticky Centipede nests. The extermination of Rivertown's citizens was caused by a mass shooting by multiple Anti-Auriellen groups (Specifically the [[Atrego]]) targeting Auriellen and Cascadan settlements, with Rivertown being one of the most affected, along with Jiharke in Level 107, with a death count of 239. Multiple charities have sprung up after the event, the most prominent being the Rivertown Survivor Association, which has a following of around 1,000.

These charities have contributed massive funds towards the restoration of Rivertown, along with other areas within Level 162 that had been affected by the terrorist attack, recieving praise from the Auriellen and Cascadan governments for their contributions towards restoring the settlement.

== <center><span style="text-shadow: 1px 1px 10px #4c6fd9;font-family:Rubik Puddles;font-size: 45px;background:linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(62, 113, 189, 1), rgba(115, 161, 230, 1), rgba(62, 113, 189, 1)); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;"> ◆ Entry and Egress. </span></center> ==
=== Entrances ===
*Walking down an out of place hallway in [[Level 30|Aquatic Cycles]] can lead into Level 162.
*Certain areas within [[Level 37|Sublimity]] can lead into Level 162.
*Entering indoor pool areas in [[Level 320|Coney Island]] can lead into Level 162.
*Areas within the [[Level 330|Lukewarm Hotel]] can lead into Level 162. Usually, these entrances manifest as hallways or archways.
*A pair of automatic sliding glass doors with a scent of mint can be found within [[Level 156|The Starlit Cinema]]; going past these doors can lead to Level 162.
=== Exits ===
*Walking through a hallway that has a constant stream of rainwater leads to [[Level 298|Watering Down]].
*Finding another pair of automatic doors can reposit entry back into [[Level 156|Old Die Young]].
*Going through an emergency exit door usually lead into [[Level 338|Two Shadows in The Sun]] although reports suggest they may also lead into [[Level 213|Imaginative Dullness]] and [[Level 163|Blissful Emptiness]].
*Areas with yellow lighting may have hallways that directly transition into [[Level 167|A Short Break]]
